"{\"uid\": \"wilx.com-2024-09-05-michigan-state-police-raise-funds-special-olympics-michigan\", \"text\": \"LANSING, Mich. (WILX) - Michigan State Police hosted a  \\\"Tip-a-Cop\\\" event at the Texas Roadhouse in Delta Township. The event raised money for the Special Olympics Michigan.  Texas Roadhouse customers who brought a special flyer with them had 10% of their food sales go towards the Special Olympics.  MSP said there are nearly 20,000 Special Olympic athletes in the state. Those athletes are able to participate year-round, free of charge, due to fundraisers like this one.  Diners could also purchase shirts, anniversary coins, and raffle tickets.  \\\"One of them we are giving away a cash prize, first place is 1,000 dollars. The second is a trophy white tail hunting trip that's in Ravenna Michigan, that's valued at about 6,000 dollars,\\\" said MSP Sergeant Blaine Bachman.  Subscribe to ourNews 10 newsletterandYouTube pageto receive the latest local news and weather.Looking to hire people, or grow your business through advertising? Gray Digital Media is your one-stop marketing solution.Learnmore.  Copyright 2024 WILX. All rights reserved.\"}"